headline: CoStar Group’s Shift to Revenue Growth Amid Net Losses Might Change The Case For Investing In CSGP
summary: CoStar Group recently reported third quarter results, highlighted by an increase in revenue to US$833.6 million but a shift from net income to a net loss year-over-year, and the company issued updated guidance for both the fourth quarter and full year 2025, anticipating further revenue growth yet forecasting a net loss. An additional share buyback saw the company repurchase over half a million shares in the third quarter, bringing total buybacks under this authorization to 1.4 million shares...
